wdi2-SH.DYN.NMRT.def: Neonatal mortality rate is the number of neonates dying before reaching 28 days of age, per 1,000 live births in a given year.
wdi2-SH.DYN.NMRT.name: Mortality rate
wdi2-SH.DYN.NMRT.source: Estimates developed by the UN Inter-agency Group for Child Mortality Estimation (UNICEF, WHO, World Bank, UN DESA Population Division) at www.childmortality.org.
